Speaker: Mr SPEAKER
Title: Unknown
text: I have to inform the House that, during the adjournment, I received from the Right Honourable W. A. Watt a letter dated the 5th July, 1929, resigning his seat as member for the electoral division of Balaclava, in the State of Victoria, and that on the 11th July I issued a writ for the election of a member to serve for the said electoral division. I hnvo received a return to that writ, and, by the endorsement thereon, it appears that Thomas Walter White has been elected. Mr WHITS made and subscribed the oath of allegiance. ASSENT TO BILLS. Speaker: Mr SPEAKER
Title: Unknown
text: I have received from the widow of the late Honourable James Hiers MCColl a letter thanking the House for its resolution of sympathy. WITHDRAWA L OF PROSECUTION. MOTION OF WANT OF CONPWBNOJ!.

Speaker: Mr THEODORE
Title: Unknown
text: I give notice that tomorrow I shall move That, by its withdrawal of the lack-out prosecution against the wealthy colliery proprietor, John Brown, after its vigorous prosecutions of trade unionists, the Government has shown that in the administration of the law it unjustly discriminates between the rich and the poor; and that as a consequence the Government has forfeited the confidence of this House.

Speaker: Mr BRUOE
Title: Unknown
text: The Deputy Leader of the Opposition having given notice of a direct motion of want of confidence in the Government I , in accordance with parliamentary practice, move That the House do now adjourn. Question resolved in the affirmative. House adjourned at 8.8 p.m.
